{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:proverbs.3",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 3,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 3 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.3.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:1",
      "text": "My son, do not forget my teaching, but let your heart keep my commandments;",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.3.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:2",
      "text": "for length of days and years of life and abundant welfare will they give you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.3.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:3",
      "text": "Let not loyalty and faithfulness forsake you; bind them about your neck, write them on the tablet of your heart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.3.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:4",
      "text": "So you will find favor and good repute in the sight of God and man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.3.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:5",
      "text": "Trust in the Lord with all your heart, and do not rely on your own insight.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.3.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:6",
      "text": "In all your ways acknowledge him, and he will make straight your paths.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.3.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:7",
      "text": "Be not wise in your own eyes; fear the Lord, and turn away from evil.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.3.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:8",
      "text": "It will be healing to your flesh and refreshment to your bones.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.3.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:9",
      "text": "Honor the Lord with your substance and with the first fruits of all your produce;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.3.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:10",
      "text": "then your barns will be filled with plenty, and your vats will be bursting with wine.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.3.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:11",
      "text": "My son, do not despise the Lord 's discipline or be weary of his reproof,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.3.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:12",
      "text": "for the Lord reproves him whom he loves, as a father the son in whom he delights.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.3.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:13",
      "text": "Happy is the man who finds wisdom, and the man who gets understanding,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.3.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:14",
      "text": "for the gain from it is better than gain from silver and its profit better than gold.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.3.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:15",
      "text": "She is more precious than jewels, and nothing you desire can compare with her.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.3.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:16",
      "text": "Long life is in her right hand; in her left hand are riches and honor.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.3.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:17",
      "text": "Her ways are ways of pleasantness, and all her paths are peace.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.3.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:18",
      "text": "She is a tree of life to those who lay hold of her; those who hold her fast are called happy.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.3.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:19",
      "text": "The Lord by wisdom founded the earth; by understanding he established the heavens;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.3.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:20",
      "text": "by his knowledge the deeps broke forth, and the clouds drop down the dew.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.3.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:21",
      "text": "My son, keep sound wisdom and discretion; let them not escape from your sight,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.3.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:22",
      "text": "and they will be life for your soul and adornment for your neck.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.3.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:23",
      "text": "Then you will walk on your way securely and your foot will not stumble.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.3.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:24",
      "text": "If you sit down, you will not be afraid; when you lie down, your sleep will be sweet.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.3.25",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:25",
      "text": "Do not be afraid of sudden panic, or of the ruin of the wicked, when it comes;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.3.26",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:26",
      "text": "for the Lord will be your confidence and will keep your foot from being caught.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.3.27",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:27",
      "text": "Do not withhold good from those to whom it is due, when it is in your power to do it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.3.28",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:28",
      "text": "Do not say to your neighbor, “Go, and come again, tomorrow I will give it”—when you have it with you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.3.29",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:29",
      "text": "Do not plan evil against your neighbor who dwells trustingly beside you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.3.30",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:30",
      "text": "Do not contend with a man for no reason, when he has done you no harm.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.3.31",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:31",
      "text": "Do not envy a man of violence and do not choose any of his ways;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.3.32",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:32",
      "text": "for the perverse man is an abomination to the Lord, but the upright are in his confidence.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.3.33",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:33",
      "text": "The Lord 's curse is on the house of the wicked, but he blesses the abode of the righteous.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.3.34",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:34",
      "text": "Toward the scorners he is scornful, but to the humble he shows favor.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.3.35",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 3:35",
      "text": "The wise will inherit honor, but fools get disgrace.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
